{{cookwork}}
{{recipe}}

'''Soupe all'Imperatrice''' is made from breast of fowl, eggs, salt, pepper, ground rice, nutmeg, clear soup stoc.

The breast is pounded and combined with a teaspoon of ground rice, an egg yolk, salt, pepper and a small amount of nutmeg.  After running the mixture through a sieve, quenelles are formed and combined with the stock to make a soup.

{{decameron}}

[[Category:Soup recipes|{{PAGENAME}}]]

{{cookwork}} {{recipe}}
Soup alla Nazionale - a patriotic Italian soup
==Ingredients== *Clear soup *Savoury [[Cookbook:custard|custard]] ==Procedure== #Make a savoury custard and divide it into three parts, one to be left white, another coloured red with tomato, and the third green with spinach. #Put a layer of each in a buttered saucepan and cook for about ten minutes #Cut it into dice, so that you have the three Italian colours (red, white, and green) together #Then put the custard into a soup tureen and pour a good clear soup over it.
{{decameron}}
[[Category:Soup recipes|{{PAGENAME}}]]

{{ingredient}}

'''Graham crackers''' were originally conceived as a "health food" made from whole wheat (specifically, [[Cookbook:Graham Flour|Graham flour]]), but have since entered the [[Cookbook:Cuisine of the United States|cuisine of the USA]] as a basic [[Cookbook:Biscuit|biscuit]] often made from highly refined [[Cookbook:Flour|flour]] with added [[Cookbook:Sugar|sugar]] or [[Cookbook:Honey|honey]].

Graham crackers are often used as an easy source of whole wheat for a recipe, by crushing for use in baked foods. They are a bit similar to the [[Cookbook:Cuisine of the United Kingdom|UK's]] digestive biscuits and [[Cookbook:Cuisine of Australia|Australia's]] whole wheat biscuits, or "wheatens".

{{Wikipedia|Graham cracker}}

Welcome to the book for the Lord of the Rings trilogy by J.R.R. Tolkien, and Middle Earth in general.  This book strives to provide a detailed source of information about Middle Earth.

== Where to Start ==
This book has been designed to handle several different types of readers of The Lord of the Rings.  Therefore, this book has several pages suggesting reading guides for the specific levels.

* [[/Introduction/Beginner|Beginner]] - Readers who are new to The Lord of the Rings.  This should be used by readers who have read only a small amount of the books or who are interested in a general overview of the storyline.

* [[/Introduction/Intermediate|Intermediate]] - Readers who have read much of The Lord of the Rings and know many of the main characters and places.  Includes characters, places, events and a more detailed view of the storyline.

* [[/Introduction/Advanced|Advanced]] - Readers who have read all of The Lord of the Rings and The Hobbit who wish to acquire detailed knowledge of the books.  Almost every topic is covered.

== Major Sections == 
{{stages}}
* [[/Books/]] - Chapter by chapter guides to the individual books {{stage short|00%|25 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Events/]] - Detailed descriptions and analyses on major and minor events in the books {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Characters/]] - Descriptions and analyses of the major and minor characters {{stage short|25%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Places/]] - Descriptions and analyses of the locations {{stage short|00%|25 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Races/]] - Information on the races of Middle Earth {{stage short|00%|25 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Animals and Plants/]] - Information on various species of and individual animals and plants {{stage short|75%|28 December 2008}}
* [[/Items/]] - Information on the various items in Middle Earth {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Languages/]] - Information on the individual languages and writing scripts {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Timeline/]] - A detailed timeline of events throughout the ages of Middle Earth {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}

== Minor Sections == 
* [[/Concepts and Ideas/]] {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Emblems and Symbols/]] {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
* [[/Constellations, Stars and Planets/]] {{stage short|00%|26 Jan 2007}}
