{|align=right |- |{{Guide to The Lord of the Rings/Character | image_character = | image_caption = Frodo (Elijah Wood) in the 2001-03 The Lord of the Rings film trilogy| character_name = Frodo Baggins| character_alias = | character_title = The Halfling, Mayor of the Shire, Ring-bearer, Elf-friend| character_race = Hobbits| character_culture = Shire-hobbits| character_birth = 22 September 2968, Third Age| character_death = | character_departure = 29 September 3021, Third Age| character_realm = The Fellowship of the Ring, The Two Towers, The Return of the King, The Silmarillion| Book(s) = | }} |}
Frodo Baggins is the primary protagonist in The Lord of the Rings. The novel depends crucially on his decisions and actions. Frodo was the son of Drogo Baggins and Primula Brandybuck, and the heir of [[Guide to The Lord of the Rings/Characters/Bilbo Baggins|Bilbo]]. Frodo was bearer of the One Ring on his journey to Mount Doom.
