The vowels {{IPA|/ɨ̞/}} and {{IPA|/ɨː/}} occur only in Northern dialects; in Southern dialects they are replaced by {{IPA|/ɪ/}} and {{IPA|/iː/}} respectively. In Southern dialects, the contrast between long and short vowels is found in stressed [[syllable]]s only; in Northern dialects, the contrast is found only in stressed ''word-final'' syllables (including monosyllabic words).

The vowel {{IPA|/ə/}} does not occur in the final syllable of words (except a few monosyllables).

