{|width=100% style="background:#DEE7F5;" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellpadding="2"
|{{Miskito_review_head|Say in Miskito:}}
{{miskito_review|What is your mother doing?|Yaptikam dia daukisa?}}
{{miskito_review|What are the children doing?|Tuktan nani ba dia daukisa?}}
{{miskito_review|Who is crying?|Ya inisa ki?}}
{{miskito_review|Is the dog playing?|Yul ba pulisa ki?}}
{{miskito_review|The dog is not playing.|Yul ba pulras.}}
{{miskito_review|It is looking for food.|Witin ba plun plikisa.}}
{{miskito_review|The children are looking for a book.|Tuktan nani ba buk kum plikisa.}}
{{miskito_review|We aren't looking for anything.|Yawan diara plikras.}}
{{miskito_review|We're speaking Miskito.|Yawan Miskitu aisisa.}}
{{miskito_review|What are the women cooking?|Mairin nani ba dia piakisa?}}
{{miskito_review|All the mangoes are very small.|Mangu nani sut sirpi pali sa.}}
{{miskito_review|These ones are not small, they're big.|Naha nani ba sirpi apia sa, tara sa.}}
{{miskito_review|Why are the women crying now?|Nanara mairin nani ba dia muni inisa?}}
{{miskito_review|Why aren't the men looking for food?|Waitna nani ba dia muni plun plikras?}}
{{miskito_review|Where are the Americans now?|Miriki nani nanara anira sa ki?}}
|}

